.TH "size_is_lt" 9 "size_is_lt" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
size_is_lt \- Returns whether a miplevel of the given size will use the lineartile (LT) tiling layout rather than the normal T tiling layout.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "bool" size_is_lt
.BI "(uint32_t width "  ","
.BI "uint32_t height "  ","
.BI "int cpp "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "width" 12
Width in pixels of the miplevel
.IP "height" 12
Height in pixels of the miplevel
.IP "cpp" 12
Bytes per pixel of the pixel format
